/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101850/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_mountains-peloton-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101850/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_mountains-peloton-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101850/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_mountains-peloton-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101850/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_mountains-peloton-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264122\">photos by Kristof Ramon, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/kramon_velophoto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">©kramon</a></figcaption></figure><p>Last Friday we got a press release saying that Scope had become an “Official Supplier Partner of WorldTour <a href=\"https://www.team-dsm.com/\">Team DSM</a>“. Not quite the same “official partner” level sponsorship deal, this relationship is said to be the Dutch pro team and Dutch wheelmaker working together based on a shared “focus on developing innovative products to maximize performance and to improve safety”.</p><p>Scope co-founder Nieck Busser last week described the partnership as “<em>driven by innovation instead of commercial [interests]…&nbsp;The competencies we developed over the years, combined with our agile way of working makes [it so] that we can quickly turn a conceptual idea into a product. We believe that this partnership brings a lot of value into our company. The innovations developed through this partnership will be the foundation for our future products.</em>”</p><figure id=\"attachment_264121\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264121\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Team DSM carbon tubular Shimano wheels at Tour de France, photo by CAuldPhoto\" width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-297x178.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-800x480.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-768x461.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-696x418.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-1068x641.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-700x420.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-297x178.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-800x480.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-768x461.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-696x418.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-1068x641.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101842/Team-DSM-carbon-tubular-wheels-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-CAuldPhoto-detail-700x420.jpg 700w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264121\">c. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/teamdsm_/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Team DSM</a>, photo by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/cauldphoto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chris Auld</a></figcaption></figure><p>In earlier flatter stages, Team DSM did appear to still be rolling on Dura-Ace carbon wheels from sponsor/”Official Partner” Shimano, with what appeared to be cotton Vittoria tubulars glued on. They then switched to family-brand PRO wheels for the time trial.</p><h3>Scope prototype wheel details</h3><figure id=\"attachment_264119\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264119\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101828/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_wet-turn.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101828/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_wet-turn.jpg\" alt=\"Scope Cycling prototype lightweight carbon climbers wheels, disc brake road tubeless at 2021 Tour de France, Team DSM, photo by Kristof Ramon, Kramo, wet riding\" width=\"1333\" height=\"1000\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06101828/Scope-Cycling-prototype-lightweight-carbon-climbers-wheels_disc-brake-tubeless-at-Tour-de-France_Team-DSM_photo-by-Kristof-Ramon_Kramon_wet-turn.jpg 1333w,https://bikerum